---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Scientific Agentic Engineering" description="About the Scientific Agentic Engineering fellowship project and its author.">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900">About</h1>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        Scientific Agentic Engineering is a
        <a href="https://bssw.io/fellows/victor-weeks" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">2026 BSSw Fellowship</a>
        project developing methodology for integrating AI agents into scientific software workflows.
      </p>

      <p>
        As AI coding agents become increasingly capable, scientific software teams face a unique challenge:
        how to leverage these tools while maintaining the correctness, reproducibility, and domain expertise
        that scientific work demands. This project provides a principled framework for navigating that challenge.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 pt-4">Author</h2>

      <p>
        <strong>Victor Weeks</strong> is a software engineer at the
        <a href="https://ncar.ucar.edu" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">NSF National Center for Atmospheric Research (NSF NCAR)</a>,
        where he works on scientific software infrastructure for the atmospheric and earth sciences community.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
